# Release changelog (Keep a Changelog)

**Read this rule before** `gh release create` or when the user asks for a commit
 + GitHub release.

Format: [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) — semantic version tags (`v1.2.0`), present tense (“Add”, not “Added”).

## Title

```
vX.Y.Z — short human summary (≤ ~60 chars)
```

## Required sections (in order)

**Include every heading below in every release.** When a section has no items, write `_None in this release._` under that heading — do not omit headings.

| Heading | Keep a Changelog type | Contents |
|--------|------------------------|----------|
| **Overview** | — | 1–3 sentences: version, theme, who should care |
| **✨ Features** | Added | New routes, profile fields |
| **🔧 Enhancements** | Changed | Improvements to existing behaviour (non-breaking) |
| **🐛 Bug Fixes** | Fixed | Bug fixes |
| **⚠️ Breaking Changes** | Removed / breaking Changed | Major bumps only; migration path |
| **🔒 Security** | Security | Auth/IAM changes (rare) |
| **📦 Infrastructure** | Changed (infra) | CDK, IAM, Lambda env, Cognito grants |
| **🧪 Testing** | — | New/changed tests |
| **📚 Documentation** | — | README, PRD, OpenAPI |
| **⬆️ Upgrade notes** | — | Numbered deploy / consumer steps |
| **🔗 Full changelog** | — | Compare link |

Separate **Overview** from emoji sections with `---`. Separate **Upgrade notes** from **Full changelog** with `---`.

Compare URL: `https://github.com/dbryant4/mealr-account-api/compare/vPREV...vNEW`

Full changelog line format: **`vPREV → vX.Y.Z`** ([compare](…))

## Writing rules

- Bullet lists; one change per bullet; lead with the **what**, then brief **why** if non-obvious.
- Reference **`VERSION`**, **`openapi/openapi.yaml`** `info.version`, and env vars when relevant.
- **Upgrade notes** must include **`./scripts/cdk.sh deploy`** (or venv `cdk deploy`) when Lambdas or IAM change; redeploy **mealr-api-gateway** when **`ApiId`** export or routing docs change.
- Align release version with **`VERSION`**, **`openapi/openapi.yaml`**, and **`semver-version.mdc`**.
- Do **not** edit past GitHub release bodies unless the user explicitly asks — add a patch release instead.

## `gh release create` template

```bash
gh release create vX.Y.Z \
  --title "vX.Y.Z — short summary" \
  --notes "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Overview

One to three sentences.

---

## ✨ Features

- …

## 🔧 Enhancements

- …

## 🐛 Bug Fixes

_None in this release._

## ⚠️ Breaking Changes

_None in this release._

## 🔒 Security

_None in this release._

## 📦 Infrastructure

- …

## 🧪 Testing

_None in this release._

## 📚 Documentation

_None in this release._

## ⬆️ Upgrade notes

1. Bump **`VERSION`** to **X.Y.Z** (already tagged).
2. `./scripts/cdk.sh deploy`
3. Redeploy **mealr-api-gateway** if `/account` mapping or `AccountApiId` wiring changed.

---

## 🔗 Full changelog

**vPREV → vX.Y.Z** ([compare](https://github.com/dbryant4/mealr-account-api/compare/vPREV...vX.Y.Z))
EOF
)"
```

## Do not

- Ship a release without a compare link or upgrade notes when deploy is required.
- Use marketing fluff without concrete bullets.
- Duplicate the entire PR description — release notes are for **operators and API consumers**, not code review.
